oakcurric:unit-967
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Using Earth's resources"@en ;
  curric:slug "using-earths-resources" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit covers crude oil, its role as a hydrocarbon source, and separation by
  fractional distillation. It explores cracking, metal reactivity, and extraction methods,
  including biological alternatives. Emphasis is on recycling, life-cycle assessments, and
  evaluating decisions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior learning from Earth's resources, where
  they explored how natural resources are used and the importance of sustainability. It deepens
  their understanding by examining the processes involved in using Earth's resources, such as
  extraction and management, and their environmental impact. This prepares pupils for the next
  unit, Atmosphere and changing climate, where they will apply their knowledge to explore how
  resource use affects the atmosphere and contributes to climate change, reinforcing the need
  for sustainable practices.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-967-1 ,
